---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Contact Honestly Profitable"
  description="Get in touch with Honestly Profitable, corrections, operator data, general questions, press and advertising inquiries, or privacy requests. We read every message."
  path="/contact"
>
  <div class="container container-narrow page-head">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Contact' }]} />
    <h1>Contact us</h1>
    <p class="lead">Questions, corrections, and feedback are genuinely welcome, and they make the site better.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="container container-narrow page-body">
    <p>
      {SITE.name} is a small, independent reference site, and accuracy matters to us. Whether you have
      spotted a number that looks off, run one of these businesses and want to share real figures, or
      simply have a question, we would like to hear from you. Email is the best way to reach us.
    </p>

    <div class="contact-card card">
      <span class="contact-label">Email us</span>
      <a class="contact-email" href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>
      <span class="contact-sub">We read every message and typically reply within 2–5 business days.</span>
    </div>

    <h2>What you can contact us about</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Corrections &amp; accuracy.</strong> Tell us the page, the specific figure you are flagging, and a source if you have one. Corrections get priority.</li>
      <li><strong>Operator insight.</strong> If you run one of these businesses, we would love your real numbers, rough startup cost, monthly earnings, time to first income, and your region. Real operator data makes the site more accurate for everyone.</li>
      <li><strong>General questions.</strong> Ask away, and share as much about your situation as you are comfortable with so we can point you to the right resource.</li>
      <li><strong>Press &amp; media.</strong> For interviews, citations, or coverage questions, email us and mention "Press" in the subject line.</li>
      <li><strong>Advertising &amp; partnerships.</strong> For advertising or partnership inquiries, email us with "Advertising" in the subject line. Note that advertising never influences our content, see our <a href="/editorial-standards">editorial standards</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Privacy requests.</strong> To ask a privacy question or exercise a data right, email us with "Privacy" in the subject line. See our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Suggest a new business</h2>
    <p>
      Want us to add a whole new business to the library? Use the
      <a href="/submit-a-business-idea">submit a business idea</a> page, it is the fastest way to get
      a suggestion in front of us.
    </p>

    <h2>What we can and cannot do</h2>
    <p>
      We read everything, though we cannot always reply individually, and response times can be longer
      during busy periods. Please note that we <strong>cannot provide personalized financial, legal,
      investment, or tax advice</strong>, and we cannot tell you whether a specific business will work
      for your exact situation, that is what qualified local professionals and your own due diligence
      are for. See our <a href="/disclaimer">disclaimer</a> for details.
    </p>

    <p class="page-updated">Last updated: July 2026 · {SITE.domain}</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .contact-card {
    padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }
  .contact-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .contact-email {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--green-dark);
    word-break: break-word;
  }
  .contact-sub {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
</style>
